<p>
<seg id=1> Palestinian leader Arafat has begun his first official trip taking off from Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=2> Gaza International Airport began operation one day before. </seg>
<seg id=3> On Wednesday, Israeli security officials watched from beside the runway as Arafat's private plane took off for Paris. </seg>
<seg id=4> Israel is responsible for safety work at this airport. </seg>
<seg id=5> The land-for-peace agreement recently signed by Israel and Palestine cleared the way for the use of Gaza International Airport. </seg>
<seg id=6> Palestinians believe that this airport symbolizes their autonomy and will significantly promote the Palestinian economy. </seg>
</p>
